/node_modules/
# Secrets must NEVER be baked into an image layer (2026-06-09 audit fix) — the
# Dockerfile does `COPY . .`, so without this the live .env (TOKEN, API keys,
# MONGO_URI) lands in the image. Inject at runtime via compose env_file instead.
.env
.env.*
*.env
# This ONE build context is shared by both images (Dockerfile -> ctf-assistant
# via `COPY . .`, and Dockerfile.ui -> ui via `COPY ui/`). Excluding all of `ui/`
# kept ui/node_modules out of the bot image but ALSO broke the ui image build
# (ui/package.json went missing -> "/ui/package.json: not found"), so the ui
# container couldn't be rebuilt at all. Exclude only the regenerated heavy dirs:
# the bot image still skips ui/node_modules, the ui build still gets its source,
# and api/utils/statistics.ts's import of ui/lib/achievements.ts stays included.
ui/node_modules/
ui/.next/
.git/
docs/
backups/
*.tsbuildinfo
yarn.lock
pnpm-lock.yaml
package-lock.json
bun.lockb
/volumes/
